## Part 2: The B2B Export Workflow (Lead to Shipment)

Follow these **6 Stages** for every international inquiry.

### Stage 1: Lead Capture & Qualification
*   **Action:** Lead fills the form on your site.
*   **HubSpot Entry:** A "Contact" and a "Deal" are created automatically.
*   **Qualification:** Check if they provided a business email. Use Apollo to see if they are a real company.

### Stage 2: The Quotation (Soft Quote)
*   **Action:** Send a "Soft Quote" with tentative pricing.
*   **HubSpot Tool:** Use **Sales > Quotes**. 
*   **Pro Tip:** Use the "Require Signature" feature (even in Free/Starter) to make it professional.

### Stage 3: Proforma Invoice (PI)
*   **Action:** Once the buyer agrees on price, issue the **Proforma Invoice**.
*   **HubSpot Tool:** Go to the "Deal" record. Click **"Create Invoice"** (using the HubSpot Commerce tool).
*   **Fields to Include:**
    *   Incoterms (FOB Latur or CIF destination port).
    *   Payment Terms (e.g., 30% Advance, 70% against BL).
    *   Bank Details (Your Avani Agro Foods bank info).

### Stage 4: Payment Verification
*   **Action:** Buyer sends the SWIFT copy or Advance Payment.
*   **HubSpot Entry:** Move the Deal Stage to **"Payment Received / Deposit Paid."** 
*   **Automation:** This can trigger a notification to your production team to start packing the Moringa/Onion powder.

### Stage 5: Logistics & Documentation
*   **Action:** Prepare the Bill of Lading (BL), Certificate of Origin, and Phytosanitary Certificate.
*   **HubSpot Tool:** Upload these documents directly to the **"Attachments"** section of the Deal. This keeps all export papers in one place forever.

### Stage 6: Shipment & Closing
*   **Action:** The container leaves the port.
*   **HubSpot Entry:** Move the Deal Stage to **"Shipped."**
*   **Follow-up:** Set a "Task" in HubSpot to remind you to call the buyer 20 days later to check if they received the goods.

